<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State <persName type="from">Bacon</persName> to Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-13"><hi rend="italic">July 13,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Rockhill is informed that Consul-General Lay has wired that the
                            viceroy paid compensation for the losses at Lienchou, as claimed. The
                            department assumes that this settlement will not preclude claims <pb facs="0426" n="320" xml:id="pg_320"/> as stated in its telegram to
                            Mr. Rockhill of June 8. These claims are about to be presented, being
                            now in a final form. Mr. Bacon requests an immediate reply.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>